30/07/2008
TEHRAN, Iran -- Turkish Foreign Minister Ali Babacan held bilateral meetings Tuesday (July 29th) in Tehran on the sidelines of the 15th Ministerial Conference of the Nonaligned Movement. Babacan discussed bilateral relations and Iran's nuclear programme during his meetings with Iranian President Mahmud Ahmadinejad and Foreign Minister Manouchehr Mottaki. Babacan urged using dialogue to solve the dispute over Iran's nuclear programme. Turkey insists the continuation of talks between Iran and western countries is essential. (Turkish Press, Hurriyet, Sabah, Zaman, Anadolu news agency - 29/07/08) 
